9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 922, L.D. 1400, “An Act to Exempt
10 Certain Public School Districts and Their Employees from the Paid Family and Medical
11 Leave Benefits Program”
12 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
13 'An Act to Exempt Certain Public School Districts and Agricultural Employers and
14 Employees from the Paid Family and Medical Leave Benefits Program'
15 Amend the bill by inserting after the enacting clause the following:
16 'Sec. 1. 26 MRSA §850-A, sub-§13, as enacted by PL 2023, c. 412, Pt. AAA, §7,
17 is amended to read:
18 13. Employee. "Employee" means a person who may be permitted, required or
19 directed by an employer in consideration of direct or indirect gain or profit to engage in
20 any employment in the State but does not include an independent contractor or any
21 individual employed in agriculture, as described in the Employment Security Law and the
22 Federal Unemployment Tax Act, 26 United States Code, Section 3311.
23 Sec. 2. 26 MRSA §850-A, sub-§14, as enacted by PL 2023, c. 412, Pt. AAA, §7,
24 is amended by amending the first blocked paragraph to read:
25 "Employer" does not include the Federal Government or any person, sole proprietorship,
26 partnership, corporation, association or other business entity that employs individuals in
27 agriculture, as described in the Employment Security Law and the Federal Unemployment
28 Tax Act, 26 United States Code, Section 3311, in this State.'
29 Amend the bill in section 3 in the 2nd line (page 1, line 17 in L.D.) by inserting after
30 the following: "districts" the following: 'and employers of individuals employed in
31 agriculture and self-employed individuals employed in agriculture'
32 Amend the bill in section 3 in the 4th line (page 1, line 19 in L.D.) by striking out the
33 following: "850-S. A school district employer" and inserting the following: '850-S or by an
34 employer of individuals employed in agriculture and self-employed individuals employed
