21 SUMMARY
2222 This amendment changes the title of the bill and excludes from the paid family and
2233 medical leave benefits program any individual employed in agriculture, including an
2244 individual self-employed in agriculture, as described by the Employment Security Law and
2255 the Federal Unemployment Tax Act. It requires the Department of Labor to refund
2266 contributions made by employers of individuals in agriculture pursuant to the paid family
2277 and medical leave benefits program. It requires an employer that deducted a portion of the
2288 premium required for an employee from that employee's wage to remit that portion of the
2299 premium to the employee as part of the employee's wage. It also adds an appropriations
3300 and allocations section.
